                <h1>Understanding Islam: A Brief Overview</h1>
                <p>Islam is a major world religion founded in the 7th century, based on the teachings of the Prophet Muhammad. It emphasizes monotheism, the belief in one God (Allah), and the importance of the Quran as the holy text. Its five pillars guide followers in faith, prayer, charity, fasting, and pilgrimage to Mecca, shaping a vibrant global community.</p>
